Adds contribution document
First commit of the kraken-biom tool
Adds unit testing framework and testing for the parse_kraken_report method.
Adds basic repo files: manifest, setup config, and changelog.
Fixes parsing code so that the min tax level parameter is not ignored.
Ensures the max and min tax levels are ordered correctly.
Adds Travis CI support.
Tests are now compatible with Python 2.
Fix for Python 2 compatibility in verbose output.
Version bump to 0.1.0
Fix for travis build, does not need to install self for testing.
Update MANIFEST.in
Renames kraken-biom.py to kraken_biom.py to comply with standard python naming conventions.
Adds Installation and Requirements sections to README.
Adds Travis CI badge to README.
Adds fully-functional setup.py to repository.

Replaces [wheel] with [bdist_wheel] in setup.cfg.

The bdist_wheel directive is the current official directive as per the
python packaging docs: https://python-packaging-user-guide.readthedocs.io/en/latest/distributing/#universal-wheels.
The [wheel] directive was the original according to https://github.com/meshy/pythonwheels/issues/71.
Renames _main() to main and updates the entry_points in setup.py.
Moves the central loop for processing kraken-report files from main() to a self-contained method.
Adds parameter descriptions to doctoring for write_biom.
Adds a program argument that enables writing a file containing just the OTU IDs from the data set.

When creating taxa strings, add empty levels after last level to fill the string out to species.

For example, for a family-level OTU, add ["g__", "s__"] to the end.
Pass max and min rank to process_samples()

Update test_parse_kraken_report_taxonomy() to reflect changes in tax_fmt().

tax_fmt() now fills out taxonomy strings so that everything from k__ to s__ is included, even if those levels are blank.
Add tests for the biom_create() method.
Add test stub for process_samples() method.
Change assertTrue to assertEqual.

Add tests to test_process_samples.

Validates sample IDs from file names and per-sample OTU counts.
Add test to test_process_samples validating parsing for a subset of the taxa from the test data.

Remove python 2.7 from the travis config.

There is an unknown issue in test_process_samples.py with writing
the kraken results to a temp file under python 2.7 that causes the parsing
method to fail. The same method is fine when run in test_parsing.py and
test_biom_create.py under python 2.7. So until I can figure out where the
problem is, I'm removing python 2.7 from the travis config.
Fix write_otu_file so the file is opened for writing, not reading. Handle file path with no dir specified.

Adds description of the taxonomy metadata.

The README now contains a paragraph mentioning that kraken-biom stores the taxonomy for each OTU in the standard QIIME format, and that other formats may be supported in the future.
Corrected version number in kraken-biom.py

Expanded installation instructions

The README file now includes instructions for installing with pip (kraken-biom now on PyPI) from PyPI and with pip directly from GitHub.

Updates conda setup.

The conda setup was updated with recommendations for Travis from Conda: http://conda.pydata.org/docs/travis.html

add failing test assertions for taxonomy parsing

Add extra classifications to the test data to trigger a failure for the
taxonomy parsing code (specifically when classifications have missing
ranks).

Fix #4: parse taxonomic level from indentation

Switch to parsing kraken-report's taxonomic hierarchy from the
indentation level of each entry's scientific name (instead of from the
named rank for a given entry).  This should handle entries with missing
named ranks.
